of Mr. Walter Skiscim at the Heritage Center. Mr. Skiscim was a beloved figure of our community, known for his remarkable Skiscim Studio & Photography, which captured countless memories for Indian River County. In a touching story of local history, Mr. Skiscim met his lovely wife at the Heritage Center during a USO dance in the 1940\u2019s. Today, black-and-white photos of him in his Navy uniform and dancing were on display at the Heritage Center, evoking cherished memories of a life well-lived. Mr. Skiscim passed on 10\/15\/24 at the young age of 99.
